# The ingestion decision sheet

| Source shape | Pick |
|---|---|
| Daily drop, few files, simple SQL | **`COPY INTO`** |
| Continuous, maybe millions, schema evolves | **Auto Loader** |
| Billion-file scale, listing too slow | **+ file notification** |
| SaaS with a managed connector | **Lakeflow Connect (managed)** |
| Relational DB with CDC | **Managed DB connector** |
| Kafka / Kinesis / Event Hubs | **Structured Streaming** |
| Long-tail SaaS, no connector | **Partner connector** |
| Operational DB, nightly snapshot | **JDBC** in a Jobs task |
| Custom REST API | Land JSON → Auto Loader |
| Small/cold, no copies allowed | **Lakehouse Federation** |

**Two pivots:** ① files in storage, or a system with an API? ② streaming, incremental, or once a day?
